  "prompt": "Is OBC quota applicable to those who sold their property?",
  "response": "The applicability of the Other Backward Classes (OBC) quota to individuals who have sold their property depends on the specific rules and regulations of the country or region in question, as well as the criteria used to determine OBC status.\n\nIn India, for example, OBC status is typically determined by social, educational, and economic criteria, rather than property ownership alone. Selling property might affect an individual's economic status, but it does not directly impact their caste or social standing, which are primary factors in determining OBC eligibility.\n\nTo provide a more accurate answer, it would be helpful to know:\n\n1. The specific country or region you are referring to.\n2. The context in which the OBC quota is being considered (e.g., educational institutions, government jobs, etc.).\n3. Any other relevant details about the individual's situation.\n\nIf you can provide more information, I can offer a more tailored response. In general, it's best to consult the relevant government authorities or legal experts in your area to understand the specific implications of selling property on OBC quota eligibility.",
